> Cook it once, eat it twice: tonight's dinner extras transform into tomorrow's lunch. What’s more comforting than a warm bowl of chili? In the winter months, there’s nothing better. Enjoy a bowl of this southwestern spiced chili tonight, and then wrap it up into a delicious cheesy burrito for lunch tomorrow. Win, Win!

Bring 1¼ cups @water{1 1/4%cups} with a pinch of @salt{pinch} to boil in a small, lidded #pot{}. Once boiling, stir in @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup}. Reduce heat to low and cook, covered, until rice is tender, about ~{15%minutes}. Keep covered.

Meanwhile, wash and dry all produce. Core, deseed, and dice @Long Green Pepper{1}(deseeded and diced). Dice @Roma Tomato{1}(diced). Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating whites from greens. Finely chop @Cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

Pat @Chicken Cutlets{20%ounce} dry with @paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and half the @Enchilada Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}. Heat a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{drizzle} in a large #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, about ~{4-7%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; remove chicken from pot and set aside.

While chicken cooks, zest 1 tsp zest from @Lime{1}(zested and quartered); quarter lime. In a small #bowl{}, combine tomato, scallion whites, up to half the cilantro, a squeeze of lime juice, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. In a separate small bowl, combine @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon}, lime zest, a squeeze of lime juice, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{drizzle} in same pot used to cook chicken over medium-high heat. Add green pepper and cook, stirring, until slightly softened, about ~{1-2%minutes}. Add @Chili Powder{1%teaspoon} and remaining Enchilada Spice. Cook, stirring, until thoroughly combined, about ~{1-2%minutes}. Add @Cannellini Beans{13.4%ounce} and their liquid, @Chicken Stock Concentrate{3%unit}, and 1 1/2 cups water. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer. Simmer until slightly thickened, about ~{7-10%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Cut chicken into bite-sized pieces (or shred with two #forks{}). Stir into chili. Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in half the scallion greens and season with salt and pepper. Reserve ⅓ of the rice and ⅓ of the chili for lunch. Divide remaining rice and remaining chili between #bowls{}. Top with salsa and crema. Sprinkle with remaining scallion greens, half the @Monterey Jack Cheese{1/2%cup}, remaining cilantro, and a squeeze of lime juice. Drizzle both bowls with @Hot Sauce{3%teaspoon}.

Divide reserved rice and chili between @Flour Tortilla{2}. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Roll tightly into burritos. Wrap in #plastic wrap{} and refrigerate overnight. When ready to eat, microwave until warmed through, about ~{1-2%minutes}. Serve with remaining hot sauce packets.